1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:03,640
<i>A:pada:m apaharta:ram</i>

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,960
<i>da:ta:ram sarva-sampada:m</i>

3
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:13,040
<i>Lo:ka:bhira:mam Sri:Ra:mam</i>

4
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:18,679
<i>bhu:yo bhu:yo nama:myaham</i>

5
00:00:23,119 --> 00:00:26,600
<i>Jai Sri:manna:ra:yana.</i>

6
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:31,519
Dear devotees,

7
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:39,760
when we set out to begin
some task,

8
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:46,320
why are we doing it?
What is its aim?

9
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:54,160
Who is involved, what must be done —
only after knowing these

10
00:00:54,160 --> 00:01:01,840
do we begin it. Likewise, when we
take up a scripture,

11
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:10,400
to read it — why should we read it,
what should we learn,

12
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:18,880
what benefit will it bring us? —
knowing this,

13
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:24,320
if we feel it will be of use to us,

14
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:30,720
then we make the chance to read it,
or to do more.

15
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:34,680
The Bhagavad <i>Gi:tha</i> too —

16
00:01:35,119 --> 00:01:40,880
for whom, and to reveal what —

17
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:47,840
knowing this, we should begin it.
Usually

18
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:53,840
everyone keeps saying, "Oh, the <i>Gi:tha</i>
is a very great scripture,"

19
00:01:53,840 --> 00:02:01,600
they keep thinking so. But what is
its purpose, and for whom?

20
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:07,200
In the <i>Gi:tha</i> there is
business management,

21
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:14,800
there is personality development,
there is science, there is philosophy,

22
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:20,800
there is theology in it,
and many morals too,

23
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:25,680
this is there, that is there,
so many things — that is how we

24
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:33,280
talk about the <i>Gi:tha</i>. But when we
touch that scripture,

25
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:39,920
what we must gain from it,
what we must learn — if we have

26
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:47,800
clarity about that, we then try
to grasp it from within it.

27
00:02:48,959 --> 00:02:54,959
Now suppose we call the Prime Minister,
"Sir, sweep the roads a little."

28
00:02:54,959 --> 00:03:01,599
If we asked that — well, he could
sweep the roads too;

29
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:07,680
he may even sweep them. But if sweeping
roads were the purpose,

30
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:13,920
you would not need that man
to do that work;

31
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:20,000
someone else would do. There are tasks
only this person can do.

32
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:26,159
So when receiving such things —
what only he can give —

33
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:34,000
is the main purpose, then we approach him;
that is how we should.

34
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:43,360
Not because we got hold of him,
to chatter about this and that,

35
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:52,720
or to set him to other work —
that only shows our own ignorance,

36
00:03:52,720 --> 00:04:01,840
our own incapacity. Now, when we take
up a scripture like the <i>Gi:tha</i>,

37
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:06,640
when we bring it up,
what is its purpose?

38
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:14,319
Merely to teach science? For that,
there are plenty of science books;

39
00:04:14,319 --> 00:04:20,479
go to them and learn all that.
You need not take the <i>Gi:tha</i>

40
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:26,960
and have to get that
from the <i>Gi:tha</i> alone.

41
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:33,440
No. Say it is to learn morals —
there are plenty of books for that;

42
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:40,639
go into them and learn
those ethics and rules there.

43
00:04:40,639 --> 00:04:47,120
No — is the <i>Gi:tha</i> meant to teach us
some management skills?

44
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:53,199
There are plenty of management courses;
go there and

45
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:58,479
they will explain all the details;
you can learn those there.

46
00:04:58,479 --> 00:05:05,440
Or to teach rules about food and such?
For that there are enough

47
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:12,000
eminent physicians; through them
you can learn and obtain those.

48
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:17,600
So, does the <i>Gi:tha</i> speak
of such things

49
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:25,039
or not? That is not the question. But if
we know the main aim of the <i>Gi:tha</i>,

50
00:05:25,039 --> 00:05:31,520
then wherever we go, whatever we see —
does it lead us toward that aim

51
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:36,800
or not? Or through it,
are we able

52
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:43,960
to attain that aim or not? —
recognizing this becomes our duty.

53
00:05:44,479 --> 00:05:48,720
What is the main aim of the <i>Gi:tha</i>?

54
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:54,639
Teaching Arjuna his duty
is one thing —

55
00:05:54,639 --> 00:06:01,120
set that aside. If He had begun
mainly only

56
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:08,240
for that, then once He finished
instructing Arjuna that day, its task

57
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:12,400
would be over. After that
it would not be needed again;

58
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:17,000
for this age it would be
of no use to us either.

59
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:25,199
No — it would have remained
confined to that one occasion.

60
00:06:25,199 --> 00:06:30,319
But the <i>Gi:tha</i> is not a scripture
spoken only for Arjuna,

61
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:37,039
only to spur him to battle.

62
00:06:37,039 --> 00:06:44,039
Then for what was it spoken?
For humankind —

63
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:49,919
from when they are born on this earth
until they pass away,

64
00:06:49,919 --> 00:06:58,319
knowing what to do makes
the tasks they must do worthy ones —

65
00:06:58,319 --> 00:07:04,880
this it must teach. And how
should those tasks be done?

66
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:12,800
The devotion to duty
that all humankind needs —

67
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:19,120
how it should be — because man
had to be taught this,

68
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:26,400
teaching that is the main purpose
of His coming as <i>Krushna</i>.

69
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:33,759
Thinking so, He took Arjuna
as a pretext, an excuse,

70
00:07:33,759 --> 00:07:39,680
arranged it that way,
and delivered this through him —

71
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:45,599
this is what we must grasp.
The other things are in it too;

72
00:07:45,599 --> 00:07:53,120
<i>Yukta:ha:ra-viha:rasya</i> — learn to eat
rightly; <i>yukta-svapna:vabo:dhasya</i> —

73
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:58,400
the "early to bed, early to rise"
sayings — those too

74
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:04,879
are there. Other rules are not absent.
But teaching those rules

75
00:08:04,879 --> 00:08:11,759
is also meant to lead somewhere —
namely, that

76
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:17,599
man must know his duty
and act upon it.

77
00:08:17,599 --> 00:08:24,479
For all humanity — to teach this,
the <i>Gi:tha</i> came.

78
00:08:24,479 --> 00:08:30,080
That is why the <i>Gi:tha</i> was
divided into three parts.

79
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:39,680
First six chapters, second six,
third six — eighteen

80
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:45,839
chapters in all.
The first six chapters

81
00:08:45,839 --> 00:08:53,120
came to establish the <i>A:thma</i>,
its true nature. These, elsewhere,

82
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:58,160
we will not find. Go into management
courses, you won't learn them;

83
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:03,680
into morals, you won't know it;
into science, even less.

84
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:09,120
Going anywhere else, it is hard
to know it. To learn that, you

85
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:15,279
must come only to the <i>Gi:tha</i>.
Coming to the <i>Gi:tha</i> and

86
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:23,440
saying "I'll seek those in it"
is folly. And saying it omits them,

87
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:30,800
raising objections against it —
that too is uncalled for.

88
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:37,839
The first six chapters were named the
<i>A:thma Shatkam</i>. The nature of the <i>A:thma</i>

89
00:09:37,839 --> 00:09:42,320
is what it explains to us.

90
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:49,839
Now the second six chapters
were named the <i>Bhakthi Shatkam</i>.

91
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:56,240
<i>Bhakthi</i> means love. Toward which
reality should this love be turned?

92
00:09:56,240 --> 00:10:03,440
Toward God. Who is God,
how is He, where

93
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:11,600
is He, what does He do, what is your
bond with Him, what must He do for you, what

94
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:17,920
you long for, the One you take refuge in —
how far is it possible? All this must be known.

95
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:26,079
To reveal all this, a six-chapter part
sits in the middle of the <i>Gi:tha</i>. Its

96
00:10:26,079 --> 00:10:31,440
name — the second <i>Shatkam</i> was
called the <i>Bhakthi Shatkam</i>.

97
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:36,480
After these were spoken,
the doubts that arose in Arjuna —

98
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:42,959
"if He explains a little, I can
listen and resolve them" —

99
00:10:42,959 --> 00:10:49,760
once that courage came, all said in the
first and second six — twelve chapters —

100
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:56,000
was once put in order
and consolidated,

101
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:00,720
and wherever there were
some stop-gaps in it,

102
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:05,839
some dots needing filling,
if any, all those too were added,

103
00:11:05,839 --> 00:11:12,880
to tell it completely. As these last
six chapters came after, it was named the

104
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:20,399
<i>Pu:rva-she:sham</i> — meaning
"the remainder of what was said before" —

105
00:11:20,399 --> 00:11:26,160
that is what it was named.
Thus in three parts it was

106
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:32,160
delivered. An eighteen-chapter scripture,
with Arjuna

107
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:39,200
taken as the occasion,
instructed by <i>Sri: Krushna</i> —

108
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:46,839
a most exalted scripture, a spiritual
scripture, the Bhagavad <i>Gi:tha</i>.

109
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:53,200
In it, the first four chapters —

110
00:11:53,200 --> 00:12:00,000
He revealed a certain grief,
a sorrow

111
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:08,399
that Arjuna had. For that sorrow
to lift, his power of discernment

112
00:12:08,399 --> 00:12:12,320
had been destroyed. Discernment
means to analyze and

113
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:16,000
look — that capacity
had diminished.

114
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:24,560
What must one analyze? One must discern
between the body and the <i>A:thma</i>.

115
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:30,560
This discerning, they say, is the very
first among the means for one to improve.

116
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:39,279
Seven means were taught: <i>vive:ka, vimo:ka,
abhya:sa, kriya, anavasa:da, kalya:na, anuddharsha</i> —

117
00:12:39,279 --> 00:12:46,720
thus seven means. Of those seven,
the very first is <i>vive:ka</i>, and with it

118
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:51,920
He began. <i>Vive:ka</i> does not
mean cleverness —

119
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:57,600
<i>vive:ka</i> means the ability
to distinguish things apart,

120
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:05,600
that is its meaning — discernment.
In what should this discernment be made?

121
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:15,120
Namely: the body and the <i>A:thma</i> are
two — begin here. How did we know this?

122
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:21,040
How do I get clarity on it? If the food
you eat is good, all is good — your thinking

123
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:25,519
is what must form in you. For your
thinking to be good, first the fuel

124
00:13:25,519 --> 00:13:33,440
put into it must be good. The fuel is
the food we eat — good food must be taken.

125
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:42,880
So what is good food? By what do we
decide the goodness of food?

126
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:51,040
Namely <i>sa:tvika, ra:jasa, ta:masa</i> —
recognizing these, whatever is unfit

127
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:58,399
we keep away; whatever is needed
we grasp and take. By such food's

128
00:13:58,399 --> 00:14:05,120
influence, the thinking that arises
in you — if you can analyze this body

129
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:12,639
and this <i>A:thma</i> both and see them,
then that is named <i>vive:ka</i>.

130
00:14:12,639 --> 00:14:18,720
It begins with what is called
<i>a:ha:ra-suddhi</i> — purity of food.

131
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:22,639
In our scriptures too, the very first
thing said is just this — "<i>a:ha:ra-</i>

132
00:14:22,639 --> 00:14:27,440
<i>suddhau sattva-suddhih;
sattva-suddhau</i>

133
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:35,880
<i>dhruva: smruthih; smruthi-lambhe
sarva-granthi:na:m vipramo:kshah.</i>"

134
00:14:36,079 --> 00:14:42,079
First, <i>a:ha:ra-suddhau</i> — if the
food is good — <i>sattva-suddhih</i>:

135
00:14:42,079 --> 00:14:48,720
the mind becomes good. <i>Sattva</i> means
the mind. Good food, good mind.

136
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:53,040
Why should the mind be good?
<i>Sattva-suddhau</i> —

137
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:59,680
<i>dhruva: smruthih</i>: it is through the
mind that <i>jna:na</i> flows into you, so this

138
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:07,279
flow of <i>jna:na</i> must run smoothly,
unobstructed — no kind of refuse

139
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:14,560
should get into it; that stream,
that current, must be clean.

140
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:18,800
It must be pure; then from within it
the water that is <i>jna:na</i>

141
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:26,560
flows freely.
If that flow runs unbroken,

142
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:32,000
without stopping again and again,
if it flows steadily,

143
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:39,360
then it is named <i>dhruva: smruthih</i> —
a steady, settled remembrance,

144
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:44,959
we say. If this proceeds rightly,
then within,

145
00:15:44,959 --> 00:15:50,880
all the doubts that exist go away;
all the knots loosen.

146
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:55,040
The direct vision of one's true nature
that should arise, arises.

147
00:15:55,040 --> 00:16:00,160
Whatever you must attain, you attain.
Whatever a human birth is meant to attain,

148
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:05,839
that you attain.
<i>Sarva-granthi:na:m vipramo:kshah</i> —

149
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:12,720
all the knots of <i>karma</i> that bind you
fall away too, and you

150
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:17,360
gain great freedom.
This the Upanishad told us.

151
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:24,160
So — purity of food: the first thing to
eat is food; without it there is no life.

152
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:31,680
So the food we take must be good —
and again, how to decide that?

153
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:38,160
For that, again, some marks
were stated in it.

154
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:45,040
<i>Ja:thithah</i> — and if someone somehow
contaminates it, those are <i>a:sraya</i> defects;

155
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:52,160
or if something falls in temporarily
and it is defiled, they call it <i>nimitta</i>.

156
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:56,639
<i>Ja:thi, a:sraya, nimitta:t,</i>

157
00:16:56,639 --> 00:17:02,680
<i>adushta:t anna:t — ka:ya-suddhih.</i>

158
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:08,880
This was named <i>vive:ka</i>. That is, things
must not be <i>ja:thi</i>-defiled. Some things

159
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:13,039
by their very nature carry
certain kinds of qualities.

160
00:17:13,039 --> 00:17:18,319
Some are pungent, some sour,
some sweet — this is naturally their

161
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:24,240
trait. Likewise, some are by nature
<i>sa:tvika</i>, some

162
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:31,360
by nature <i>ra:jasa</i>, some by nature
<i>ta:masa</i>. Those that are so by nature —

163
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:37,919
whichever is <i>sa:tvika</i> for you,
those you should carefully

164
00:17:37,919 --> 00:17:43,200
select, pick up.
The <i>ja:thi</i>-defiled ones,

165
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:48,880
do not let them come near.
So — <i>ja:thi, a:sraya</i>:

166
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:55,679
whoever handles it, whoever it reaches
you through — such persons'

167
00:17:55,679 --> 00:18:01,679
influence too inevitably falls
upon that substance at times, so

168
00:18:01,679 --> 00:18:08,720
such a one — one without right
thinking, without proper

169
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:16,480
devotion, without proper fitness —
by the handling of such people,

170
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:23,679
by their contact, see that this substance
is not spoiled. <i>A:sraya-adushta:t; ja:thi-</i>

171
00:18:23,679 --> 00:18:30,480
<i>adushta:t; a:sraya-adushta:t;
nimitta-adushta:t.</i>

172
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:37,039
<i>Nimitta</i> means something fell into it
temporarily — some insect fell in,

173
00:18:37,039 --> 00:18:43,039
an ant fell in, a hair fell in,
a nail fell in,

174
00:18:43,039 --> 00:18:50,559
something falling in temporarily,
or mixing in, or being met with — the

175
00:18:50,559 --> 00:18:57,200
defects that arise from that. This we
call a <i>nimitta</i> defect. By such a <i>nimitta</i>

176
00:18:57,200 --> 00:19:03,679
too, that which is not spoiled —
<i>ja:thi-adushta:t, a:sraya-adushta:t,</i>

177
00:19:03,679 --> 00:19:10,960
<i>nimitta-adushta:t anna:t</i> —
taking such food as fuel,

178
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:16,919
then, if it is supplied
to the running of this body,

179
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:22,000
<i>ka:ya-suddhih</i> —
your body becomes well,

180
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:26,720
good — it becomes one that obeys,
that does as you say.

181
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:30,880
If the body obeys,
then the mind obeys.

182
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:37,200
If the mind obeys, then from it
the stream of <i>jna:na</i> flows. If it runs

183
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:42,400
unbroken, the bondage of <i>karma</i> loosens;
once that bondage is gone,

184
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:46,160
whatever should be seen within,
that is seen.

185
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:53,840
The very first thing taught here is
<i>vive:ka</i> — see that your food is good.

186
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:59,600
Even our worldly folk said the same:
"if there is food, there is muscle,

187
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:05,440
and he with muscle is the real man."
The food must be good. Whatever you

188
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:10,559
desire, that — if you want muscle,
muscle; if not,

189
00:20:10,559 --> 00:20:16,240
if you want a head, a head; intellect,
intellect; something else, something else.

190
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:20,400
So the food that can give you
whatever you desire

191
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:28,640
is very important.
So this was named <i>vive:ka</i>.

192
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:36,080
He tried to instill this <i>vive:ka</i> in
the second chapter. In the third,

193
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:39,600
with the <i>vive:ka</i> thus gained,
the deeds you must

194
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:46,720
perform — what are they?
He named that <i>Karma Yo:ga</i>.

195
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:54,000
You must do tasks; the body is made
for tasks, so do them. But those

196
00:20:54,000 --> 00:21:01,760
tasks — you must know how. All of them
must be done with awareness, so that

197
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:09,679
awareness He named <i>jna:na</i>.
Tasks refined by this <i>jna:na</i>

198
00:21:09,679 --> 00:21:17,679
must be done — this He said in chapter
three. What kind of awareness? Again, that is

199
00:21:17,679 --> 00:21:24,400
a big question. What should it be like?
It must be free of desire-driven intent.

200
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:30,960
He set a qualification for it —
in it you must have no kind of desire

201
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:36,559
whatsoever; the intention "this is
for me alone" must be shed.

202
00:21:36,559 --> 00:21:44,960
<i>Yasya sarve sama:rambha:h ka:ma-sankalpa-
varjita:h</i> — if it is not defiled

203
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:52,240
by one's desires — then "I," "mine,"
"for me": three dangers — "I am the doer,"

204
00:21:52,240 --> 00:22:00,720
"all this is mine," "it is all because
of me" — such notions form in us. So from

205
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:05,440
such things — if you can keep
the work you do in a state freed,

206
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:08,440
freed from them,

207
00:22:08,799 --> 00:22:15,679
then it is like a great <i>Agniho:tra</i> — as
the sacred fire burns the kindling that falls in,

208
00:22:15,679 --> 00:22:21,679
or the cotton, and casts it away —
so every task you then do,

209
00:22:21,679 --> 00:22:29,840
<i>sarve sama:rambha:h</i> —
whatever the task, by the fire that is

210
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:35,120
<i>jna:na</i>, it becomes
well-refined <i>karma</i>.

211
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:40,240
If you act knowing this — letting go
of desire-driven intents — do those tasks,

212
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:46,000
do them freely. <i>Krushna</i> never said to
give up tasks that must be done — but behind it,

213
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:51,520
He did say to give up what must go.
What must you give up? The

214
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:57,120
attachment you have to the action —
let that go. Now do your tasks.

215
00:22:57,120 --> 00:23:04,080
What happens then? Like an <i>Agniho:tra</i>,
they burn up all your obstacles,

216
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:10,880
cast them away, make them vanish.
Now begin doing your tasks.

217
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:18,400
These tasks He named <i>karma</i>. What is kept
behind — free of desire-driven intent,

218
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:24,320
that awareness which must be so —
He named <i>jna:na</i>.

219
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:30,559
Now there is <i>karma</i>, there is <i>jna:na</i> —
these two. <i>Karma</i> done; <i>jna:na</i>

220
00:23:30,559 --> 00:23:36,159
gained within. And what is gained
must become steady. Once steady,

221
00:23:36,159 --> 00:23:44,080
it must ripen into faith; that faith
must become full of love. Then do these tasks.

222
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:49,520
Then every task you do brings, to the
one on the other side who receives it,

223
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:57,120
joy. That tasks be done thus —
this He said in the third chapter.

224
00:23:57,120 --> 00:24:02,799
God showed us such a one — He Himself
came that day as <i>Krushna</i>,

225
00:24:02,799 --> 00:24:08,640
and today, for us, stands as the
<i>archa:-mu:rthi</i> — in the deity's form, in worship

226
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:14,000
He receives it. Thus all
the tasks you do —

227
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:19,760
how to do them, with what to do them —
this He told us.

228
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:25,600
When He said this, the Arjuna who heard
stays only within his own view; rather than

229
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:31,440
heed the words of the one speaking —
that did not much register with him.

230
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:38,480
Right then he only wants to pour out
his own fuss, his own feelings, rather than

231
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:46,640
"let me listen a little to what is said
and reflect" — that state being absent, He

232
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:52,400
seems to be saying tasks must be done.
But behind it, awareness is paramount,

233
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:57,360
He seems to say. "Awareness is paramount,
so let me fix my mind on awareness," he thinks.

234
00:24:57,360 --> 00:25:01,200
"Then, work — the more you give it up,
the more you reduce it,

235
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:06,400
the more the ease," it seems to him.
"So somehow I must give this up; somehow

236
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:11,520
on <i>jna:na</i> I must depend." Now, "there are
two things," you say — yes. What are they? Work

237
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:18,080
is there, awareness is there;
<i>karma</i> is there, <i>jna:na</i> is there — these two.

238
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:25,039
"Now how do we manage both?"
Well, work must be done. But how

239
00:25:25,039 --> 00:25:30,960
to do it? Behind it must be powerful
<i>jna:na</i>. "So which is paramount?" — <i>jna:na</i> is very

240
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:36,880
paramount, sir. "Oho — since the wealth
of <i>jna:na</i> is paramount, then I need not work."

241
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:45,360
He listens to His words; they seem
to make sense, but to ponder and

242
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:52,080
settle it within — lacking the capacity
for that, only halfway

243
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:55,279
does he understand. By what he understood,
he raises questions.

244
00:25:55,279 --> 00:25:59,760
To somehow make it clear to him —
that is the yearning

245
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:05,520
of <i>Sri: Krushna</i>. The third chapter
ended thus. <i>Jna:na</i>

246
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:10,720
is very paramount indeed, He said;
and one wished to learn still more of it.

247
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:15,760
He explained the whole
of the fourth chapter.

248
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:21,120
He told how important <i>jna:na</i> is;
having said all that, at the end —

249
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:27,919
"since you have learned how great <i>jna:na</i>
is, get up and work," He said. "<i>Jna:na</i> is great,

250
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:32,159
yet You tell me to work again?
If <i>jna:na</i> is so great, I would gladly

251
00:26:32,159 --> 00:26:36,320
give up everything, sit nicely,
and just meditate like that,

252
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:44,880
do meditation," I think — but again,
"<i>uttishtha — uttishtha, Bha:rata!</i>"

253
00:26:44,880 --> 00:26:52,000
He said, in the fourth chapter.
"So — do you say <i>jna:na</i>, or <i>karma</i>? Of these

254
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:56,720
two, which exactly is right now —
I cannot understand, sir. Will You

255
00:26:56,720 --> 00:27:04,640
make it clear?" — as he prays thus,
chapter five of the <i>Gi:tha</i> begins.

256
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:12,120
Let us learn the question;
let us learn the answer. <i>Jai Sri:manna:ra:yana.</i>
